    "The emergence of some latticebased cryptographic schemes here demonstrates higher efficiency compared to traditional schemes based on RSA.",
    "In a more specific context, this implementation surpasses a comparable RSA implementation by an order of magnitude in terms of speed, affords a heightened level of security while demanding fewer device resources.",
    "Nonetheless, it will take a while before lattice-based schemes start to replace existing public-key cryptography.",
    "For instance, ECC was introduced by Miller (1985) and Koblitz (1987), but it took nearly two decades to become integrated into actual secure systems.",
    "While the security analysis of cryptographic schemes is an essential consideration, the paramount challenge for lattice-based cryptography thus far has been its practicality."
